      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Trend assessment\n- Theory: en is neutral, so M2+ + nL0 ⇌ MLn2+ has the same net charge on both sides (Δ∑z² ≈ 0). Debye–Hückel/SIT therefore predicts minimal ionic‑strength dependence of log β for ML, ML2, and ML3.\n- SRD‑46 notes for this pair are consistent with that expectation: reported Ni–en log β values in common aqueous media (e.g., NaClO4, NaNO3) change only slightly from low ionic strength to roughly 1 M; medium‑specific effects can be as large as, or larger than, the small I‑effects.\n- Practical implication: Within a single background electrolyte, log β for Ni(en)n2+ is nearly constant with I (small drifts at most). Comparing across different electrolytes can obscure any weak slope because medium‑specific interactions shift the baseline.",
